Mainland
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the South Island (orig. by South Islanders, but ironically, then almost neutrally, by North Islanders: now in general humorous or light-hearted colloquial application)
Origin:
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: 1952 See large and humorous correspondence in Auckland <i>The Herald </i>or <i>Star</i> in Dec 1952 (in S Kits from PSA)
